    <title>Chicken Soup with Rice</title>

    <comment></comment>
    <thumbnail>../images/placeholder.png</thumbnail>
    <image></image>
    <category></category>
    <yield></yield>
    <prepTime></prepTime>
    <cookTime></cookTime>
    <part></part>



    <ingredient>3 TBsp olive oil</ingredient>
    <ingredient>2Lt chicken stock</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1 store bought chicken meat shredded </ingredient>
    <ingredient>4 -6 cloves garlic crushed </ingredient>
    <ingredient>1 bulb fennel sliced</ingredient>
    <ingredient>2 large carrots chopped </ingredient>
    <ingredient>2 sticks celery chopped</ingredient>
    <ingredient>2 zucchini chopped</ingredient>
    <ingredient>2 corn cobs corn removed </ingredient>
    <ingredient>4 sprigs thyme leaves removed</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1 bunch parsley chopped </ingredient>
    <ingredient>2 bay leaves</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1 cup arborio rice</ingredient>
    <ingredient>salt and pepper to taste </ingredient>

    <step>
Heat oil in large pot and cook garlic on low for 5 minutes. Add fennel , celery and carrot and cook for a few more minutes. Then add bay leaves, thyme, zucchini and corn, cook for 1 minute more. Add broth* chicken and salt and pepper bring to the boil then simmer for 20- 30 minutes. Just before serving add parsley and stir well. Serve with a sprinkle of Parmesan sprinkled on top and crusty bread if desired. 
</step>

<step>*add additional water if necessary to ensure all meat and veggies are covered</step>

</recipe>